### Desktop view device #####

We need to install Remmina

sudo apt install remmina


### To connecting device (i.e.) Desktop sharing device ###

Setting -> sharing -> screen sharing -> turn ON

In case we are not able to turn on, follow below instruction.

Cannot turn on sharing on ubuntu 18.04

After I turn on the slider, nothing happen. When i exit the window and go back to it, it turned off again. 
I want to use screen sharing. What do I have to do ? Image after turn on the slider

The screen sharing is featured by Vino vnc server, you just have to install it

sudo apt install vino

FYI, The ssh server (too) can be enabled/disabled on this gnome settings section
